  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p>The resort offers a choice of seven restaurants offering a buffet or table service:</p>
<p><strong>Les Bouches</strong> has a panoramic terrace offering beautiful views over the straits of Bonifacio. The restaurant serves an extensive buffet breakfast and in the evening guests can enjoy a beautifully presented buffet of delicious foods. The restaurant also has show cooking displays for guests to watch. </p>
<p><strong>Nautilus</strong> is the resorts main restaurant that looks out over the beachfront pool. The restaurant serves buffet breakfasts and dinners. Here guests can enjoy a wide choice of Mediterranean and Sardinian Cuisine. </p>
<p><strong>Il Grecale </strong>restaurant overlooks the little bays surrounding the resort. Guests can enjoy a candle lit meal overlooking the water. The restaurant served a variety of international dishes as well as traditional Sardinian dishes. (Reservation required)</p>
<p><strong>La Prua</strong> restaurant is located on the terrace overlooking the beachfront pool. Watch as the chef creates delicious Mediterranean dishes for you to try, whilst you enjoy a glass of wine from their excellent selection. (on reservation and with supplement)</p>
<p><strong>Li Ciusoni</strong> authentic Sardinian cuisine, including traditional dishes of Gallura made with fresh local produce (on reservation and with supplement).</p>
<p><strong>Lin Zini</strong> is located in a romantic spot right on the beach front.  It offers exclusive dinnersSpecialising in barbecue, serving shellfish and fresh fish of the day (on reservation and with supplement; opening subject to weather conditions).</p>
<p><strong>Restaurant pizzeria</strong> at the Mini Club with a wooden fire oven and grill, dedicated to children.</p>
<p><strong>Conchiglia Swim-up bar </strong>Enjoy a refreshing drink without even leaving the pool. </p>
<p><strong>Snack bars </strong>there are also two snack bars serving light refreshments. </p>
<p><strong><u>Sporting Activities</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Four Swimming Pools</li>
<li>Fitness Room (a free equipped gym area aside from a cardio fitness room (on payment) at the Wellness Centre)</li>
</ul>
<p>Sporting activities are payable at a local rate:</p>
<ul>
<li>Golf Course and Lessons (Free for children up to 13 years old)</li>
<li>Kayaking</li>
<li>Mountains Bikes</li>
<li>Boat charter</li>
<li>Sports fishing – including deep water fishing</li>
<li>Windsurfing, sailing and kite surf lessons at a famous ‘Surfers Haven’ (15km away) school</li>
<li>Diving at qualified school in Santa Teresa Gallura (transfer to Porto Pollo and Santa Teresa Gallura on payment)</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thalasso Spa</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Le Thermae</strong> Thlasso Spa is located in a beautiful natural setting in the gardens of the resort. It is surrounded by striking granite rocks. The spa includes Turkish bath, sauna, Beatty treatments and massage treatments. (All payable at a local rate)</p>]]></facilityDescription>
  <familyDescription><![CDATA[<p>Resort Valle dell’Erica offers plenty of amenities for its youngers guests. Choose from a range of chidren’s clubs and rooms that can accommodate up to four people - there’s also family-friendly entertainment in the evenings. Parents can use equipment such as highchairs, push chairs, sterilisers, bottle warmers, baby intercom phones, changing tables and cots free of charge (pew-booking may be required).</p>
<p><strong>The Nursery</strong> is available for parents with babies under two and has everything necessary for feeding babies including vegetable soups and purées, fruit, milk, water and fruit juices.</p>
<p><strong>Baby Club</strong> caters for ages 2-3 years and is payable locally (pre-booking is required)</p>
<p><strong>Mini Club</strong> is free of charge for ages 4-9 years. Open between 9am and 11pm they organise a range of fun activities including volleyball, football, watersports and creative workshops.</p>
<p>From ages 10-13 years, children can enjoy snorkelling, canoeing, golf lessons, volleyball and the games room with Nintendo, Wii, Playstation and Xbox free of charge.</p>]]></familyDescription>
